Solution:
We first note that $\triangle ACD$ is a $5$-$12$-$13$ right triangle, so $\angle CAD = \sin^{-1} \frac{12}{13}.$

[asy]
pair A, B, C, D;
A=(12,0);
D=(0,0);
C=(0,5);
B=(0,9);
draw(A--B--C--A--D--C);
draw((0,.5)--(.5,.5)--(.5,0));
label("$A$", A, dir(-45));
label("$B$", B, dir(135));
label("$C$", C, dir(180));
label("$D$", D, dir(-135));
label("$15$", A/2, dir(90));
label("$13$", (A+C)/2, dir(180));
label("$5$", (C+D)/2, dir(180));
label("$9$", (B+C)/2, dir(90));
[/asy]

Then $\angle CAB = 90^\circ - \angle CAD = \cos^{-1} \frac{12}{13},$ so
\[[ABC] = \frac{1}{2} \cdot AB \cdot AC \cdot \sin \angle CAB = \frac{1}{2} \cdot 15 \cdot 13 \cdot \frac{12}{13} = \boxed{90}.\]

